1
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:14,458
<i>[Man narrating]
During the Warring States Period,</i>

2
00:00:14,750 --> 00:00:18,333
<i>China was made up of
dozens of nations.</i>

3
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:21,500
<i>Countless fights between states.</i>

4
00:00:21,792 --> 00:00:23,583
<i>Society was in devastation.</i>

5
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:33,500
<i>The 7 largest states were known as
Qi, Chu, Yan, Han, Zhao, Wei and Qin.</i>

6
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,375
<i>The rest was nearly wiped out</i>

7
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:40,708
<i>a hundred years before the unification.</i>

8
00:00:43,708 --> 00:00:48,208
<i>Qin then conquered Han and Zhao
subsequently.</i>

9
00:00:59,292 --> 00:01:01,958
<i>Year 227 B.C.</i>

10
00:01:02,167 --> 00:01:05,042
<i>When Wei's troops marching towards
the state of Liang.</i>

11
00:01:05,708 --> 00:01:10,250
<i>they were ambushed by Liang
at Mt. Phoenix.</i>

12
00:01:10,625 --> 00:01:12,167
<i>Both sides suffered heavily.</i>

13
00:01:12,583 --> 00:01:17,250
<i>Death toll reached 3,000.</i>

14
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:28,583
SDH/Translation: Arigon

15
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:38,875
[Crow gargling]

16
00:01:45,958 --> 00:01:47,541
[Crow gargling]

17
00:01:52,125 --> 00:01:56,083
[Wolf howling]

18
00:02:03,166 --> 00:02:06,291
[Crow gargling]

19
00:02:09,291 --> 00:02:10,875
[Crow gargling]

20
00:02:24,416 --> 00:02:31,708
[Crow continues gargling]

21
00:02:36,291 --> 00:02:39,416
[Spring bouncing]

22
00:02:53,791 --> 00:02:55,125
Third bro.

23
00:02:58,458 --> 00:03:00,125
Third bro.

24
00:03:01,416 --> 00:03:03,500
You're not lucky as I am.

25
00:03:16,625 --> 00:03:18,208
[Crow gargling]

26
00:03:28,750 --> 00:03:30,750
Big soldier: General!
Man: Who are you?

27
00:03:30,916 --> 00:03:32,750
Liang's soldier.

28
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:46,708
[Man gasping]

29
00:03:52,541 --> 00:03:53,708
[Yelling]

30
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,208
[Spring bouncing]

31
00:04:09,916 --> 00:04:13,291
[Yelling]

32
00:04:29,625 --> 00:04:31,291
[Groaning in pain]

33
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:47,625
[Both yelling]

34
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:53,250
[Groaning]

35
00:05:03,375 --> 00:05:07,000
[Groaning in pain]

36
00:05:25,583 --> 00:05:32,041
<i>[Big Soldier singing]
One main road leads to homecoming</i>

37
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:39,374
<i>My home is right at
the foot of Mt. Liang</i>

38
00:05:40,583 --> 00:05:47,291
<i>Soils are rich there
5 acres of farms</i>

39
00:05:47,624 --> 00:05:49,166
Pretty good.

40
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:55,416
<i>5 acres of farm
What to grow?</i>

41
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:03,916
[Big Soldier]
Let me tell you something.

42
00:06:03,999 --> 00:06:06,583
When I was a boy, I caught a boar.
My dad had me let go of it.

43
00:06:06,749 --> 00:06:08,499
You know why?

44
00:06:08,624 --> 00:06:10,624
There were boys
inside that belly.

45
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:12,624
You have boys, huh?

46
00:06:16,749 --> 00:06:18,458
You know what,

47
00:06:19,083 --> 00:06:22,291
you're my captive now.
Hey, hey.

48
00:06:22,999 --> 00:06:24,374
[Groaning]

49
00:06:24,458 --> 00:06:26,333
You've lost few blood.

50
00:06:26,708 --> 00:06:28,916
Not a big deal.

51
00:06:30,708 --> 00:06:33,041
This is the drug developed
by my family.

52
00:06:33,208 --> 00:06:35,291
Don't spare this to anyone.

53
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:40,624
You hurt, huh?

54
00:06:41,291 --> 00:06:43,458
Now it gonna hurt more.

55
00:06:43,541 --> 00:06:45,624
[Groaning in great pain]

56
00:06:45,708 --> 00:06:48,208
You're welcome, young man!

57
00:06:48,499 --> 00:06:52,166
Big Soldier: You'll live, you know.
Wei's General: X+@#?

58
00:06:52,708 --> 00:06:54,374
And don't curse.

59
00:07:00,499 --> 00:07:01,874
My dad said,

60
00:07:02,124 --> 00:07:06,291
Scratch when you're itchy,
Smile when you ain't lucky!

61
00:07:09,791 --> 00:07:11,333
Pretty good.

62
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:13,416
Mmm?

63
00:07:13,624 --> 00:07:14,666
[Yelling]

64
00:07:25,083 --> 00:07:26,124
[Moaning]

65
00:07:30,749 --> 00:07:32,416
[Blood splashing]
Ah!

66
00:07:42,624 --> 00:07:44,208
General.

67
00:07:48,291 --> 00:07:49,374
Deputy General Yu.

68
00:07:49,499 --> 00:07:51,124
Yu:
Yes, I am.

69
00:07:50,999 --> 00:07:53,166
Wei's General:
Hang on a sec.

70
00:07:54,458 --> 00:07:56,666
Wei's General:
Why you're here?

71
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:59,416
Yu:
In pursuit of Liang's men.

72
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:05,833
Wei's General: In pursuit?
How many have you killed?

73
00:08:05,916 --> 00:08:07,166
Wei's General:
Speak.

74
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:08,458
Yu: One.

75
00:08:08,666 --> 00:08:11,374
- My men must fight hard.
Yu: Liang's came hard on us...

76
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:12,999
Wei's General:
Defend our nation with our lives.

77
00:08:13,124 --> 00:08:16,999
Yu: Please, for the sake of...
- AWOL personnel must face penalty.

78
00:08:17,166 --> 00:08:21,416
Yu: General, my company was
all gone last night.

79
00:08:21,541 --> 00:08:25,208
Wei's General:
Gone? I was there last night.

80
00:08:25,374 --> 00:08:27,583
In fact, we were ambushed.

81
00:08:27,791 --> 00:08:30,041
And you were the traitor.

82
00:08:41,958 --> 00:08:44,124
You're so cruel.

83
00:08:44,249 --> 00:08:46,916
He saved your life, and you took his.

84
00:08:48,541 --> 00:08:49,874
Hey, hey, hey,

85
00:08:49,999 --> 00:08:52,124
what you gonna do, huh?

86
00:08:53,041 --> 00:08:54,249
He was right.

87
00:08:54,457 --> 00:08:56,499
You're all dead.

88
00:08:56,791 --> 00:08:58,249
Kill me.

89
00:08:58,457 --> 00:09:00,416
I don't kill POW.

90
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:05,249
Now, keep begging. I might let
you go, if you tried hard enough.

91
00:09:05,416 --> 00:09:07,291
Wei's General:
Just kill me.

92
00:09:08,791 --> 00:09:10,291
You really want to die?

93
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,582
Here, let me help you.

94
00:09:18,249 --> 00:09:19,499
Too bad,

95
00:09:20,499 --> 00:09:23,166
I failed my mission.

96
00:09:46,249 --> 00:09:48,332
[Big Soldier chuckling]
Want to die, huh?

97
00:09:48,374 --> 00:09:50,541
Die another day.

98
00:10:05,874 --> 00:10:09,582
Prince Wen, we've accomplished.

99
00:10:10,416 --> 00:10:14,957
Like he said, to die with
dignity in a battle field.

100
00:10:15,291 --> 00:10:16,541
You're AWOL.

101
00:10:16,749 --> 00:10:18,749
Big Soldier:
Not exactly. Just playing dead.

102
00:10:18,874 --> 00:10:20,916
My dad said, no shame for
living to fight another day,

103
00:10:21,082 --> 00:10:22,374
only for being dead in vain.

104
00:10:22,582 --> 00:10:25,457
Poor Third bro didn't listen to me.
He refused to play dead.

105
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:28,082
- How much am I worth?
- It doesn't hurt to tell you.

106
00:10:28,291 --> 00:10:30,874
General alive: 5 acres of farm land.

107
00:10:30,999 --> 00:10:32,207
5 acres, eh.

108
00:10:32,332 --> 00:10:34,457
I have a jade medal in possession.

109
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:39,749
How much is this broken thingy worth?

110
00:10:39,957 --> 00:10:41,582
A lot.

111
00:10:42,749 --> 00:10:44,957
I'll keep it as a gift.

112
00:10:45,666 --> 00:10:47,624
But I don't believe you.

113
00:10:51,832 --> 00:10:54,832
Wei's soldier:
He's one of us. Still alive.

114
00:10:55,041 --> 00:10:57,957
We were ambushed...
[Groans in great pain]

115
00:10:58,374 --> 00:11:01,499
[Thundering]

116
00:11:09,332 --> 00:11:10,582
Big Soldier:
Anybody home?

117
00:11:19,291 --> 00:11:20,957
Anybody home?

118
00:11:26,166 --> 00:11:31,166
[Gasping]
[Moaning]

119
00:11:32,624 --> 00:11:36,207
Somebody, bring me meatloaf and liquor!

120
00:11:36,791 --> 00:11:37,832
Hey.

121
00:11:38,041 --> 00:11:41,124
A big shot like you,
what would you say now, huh?

122
00:11:41,166 --> 00:11:43,957
"Absurd!
Take him outside for beheading."

123
00:11:56,749 --> 00:11:58,916
<i>Big Soldier:
Nothing to eat in here.</i>

124
00:12:12,582 --> 00:12:15,999
Whoa! Hmm...

125
00:12:21,582 --> 00:12:23,790
[Yelling]

126
00:12:33,499 --> 00:12:35,707
Woman:
General, spare me.

127
00:12:36,957 --> 00:12:37,874
[Sighs]

128
00:12:37,999 --> 00:12:40,082
Wu: Liang's archer and infantry unit;
2,000 men in total.

129
00:12:40,249 --> 00:12:42,207
Ambushed our 1,000-strong elite unit.

130
00:12:42,415 --> 00:12:44,332
Both sides were totally wiped out.

131
00:12:44,540 --> 00:12:46,540
Prince Wen:
This is the sword I gave him.

132
00:12:47,874 --> 00:12:49,374
But where is he now?

133
00:12:49,665 --> 00:12:51,374
Wu:
I believe we will find him.

134
00:12:52,249 --> 00:12:53,874
Prince:
Wu,

135
00:12:56,457 --> 00:12:59,665
only if he's still among the living.

136
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:05,790
Big Soldier:
War is everywhere now,

137
00:13:06,707 --> 00:13:09,290
where else you can go?

138
00:13:10,374 --> 00:13:12,207
Woman:
General, have you heard of Shen Shu?

139
00:13:12,415 --> 00:13:15,124
The one in Mt. Phoenix?
A fortunate-telling tree.

140
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:18,915
Is he your captive?

141
00:13:19,582 --> 00:13:21,790
He's my good luck.

142
00:13:22,624 --> 00:13:25,165
Hang in there.
We're almost there.

143
00:13:25,374 --> 00:13:27,165
Wei's General:
How far?

144
00:13:27,374 --> 00:13:28,874
2 days.
[Groans]

145
00:13:34,582 --> 00:13:35,540
Small potato.

146
00:13:35,707 --> 00:13:36,957
Don't make me do this.

147
00:13:38,790 --> 00:13:39,957
Don't.

148
00:13:43,540 --> 00:13:45,582
Don't push your luck.

149
00:13:47,999 --> 00:13:49,540
Wei's General:
Give me liquor.

150
00:13:49,915 --> 00:13:52,249
- No can do.
- Liquor.

151
00:14:01,124 --> 00:14:02,874
Woman:
You've fought many battles, haven't you?

152
00:14:03,082 --> 00:14:06,915
Big Soldier: Many.
You can say I'm a big time warrior.

153
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:09,207
[Wei's General whispering]
Untie me.

154
00:14:10,582 --> 00:14:12,374
Woman:
Then you must have killed a lot.

155
00:14:12,540 --> 00:14:13,707
Big Soldier:
Just too many.

156
00:14:13,874 --> 00:14:17,124
Fought against 8 men at a time.
Like yesterday.

157
00:14:17,332 --> 00:14:19,915
[Door falls]

158
00:14:21,499 --> 00:14:23,249
[Raining]

159
00:14:23,790 --> 00:14:25,790
Woman:
General, would you take me too?

160
00:14:25,999 --> 00:14:27,790
I'd like to become your captive.

161
00:14:31,582 --> 00:14:32,999
Okay.

162
00:14:33,457 --> 00:14:35,999
I know some musical.

163
00:14:36,207 --> 00:14:39,540
General, keep drinking.
I'll entertain you.

164
00:14:42,749 --> 00:14:44,915
[Woman singing]

165
00:14:45,290 --> 00:14:50,749
Man: If he turns out to be alive, what then?
Wu: Keep in mind that he's already dead.

166
00:14:51,707 --> 00:14:54,832
[Woman continues singing]

167
00:15:21,707 --> 00:15:23,165
[Groaning]

168
00:15:40,665 --> 00:15:41,915
[Slapping]

169
00:15:43,207 --> 00:15:45,082
[Big Soldier whispering]
Why?

170
00:15:46,665 --> 00:15:50,290
[Woman speaking softly]
General, you've killed so many.

171
00:15:50,748 --> 00:15:52,998
[Mumbling]
I'm not a General.

172
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:59,165
My family were killed by yours.

173
00:15:59,748 --> 00:16:01,873
And I live to sing against my will.

174
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:03,582
I'm supposed to give you a good time

175
00:16:03,748 --> 00:16:05,832
and serve you, General.

176
00:16:08,832 --> 00:16:11,748
I didn't take pleasure in
drinking with you.

177
00:16:11,873 --> 00:16:12,915
[Groaning]

178
00:16:53,790 --> 00:16:55,623
[Groaning]

179
00:17:07,457 --> 00:17:09,498
Hey, no more fight.

180
00:17:32,957 --> 00:17:34,207
Big Soldier:
Huh?

181
00:17:41,748 --> 00:17:44,873
[Instrumental music playing]

182
00:17:48,832 --> 00:17:53,082
Big Soldier:
Hey! Open the gate. I'm a soldier.

183
00:17:53,207 --> 00:17:55,582
I have taken a Wei's General...
[Gate opens]

184
00:17:55,790 --> 00:17:57,373
[Music stops]

185
00:18:05,540 --> 00:18:08,665
[Instrumental music playing]

186
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:13,582
Man in wagon:
Stop.

187
00:18:18,082 --> 00:18:19,540
Guard:
Whose this head?

188
00:18:19,707 --> 00:18:21,832
Big Soldier:
A General of Wei.

189
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:26,915
[Crowd whispering]

190
00:18:27,957 --> 00:18:30,290
That's him. I'm sure.

191
00:18:30,457 --> 00:18:33,040
That's a head of Wei's General.

192
00:18:33,165 --> 00:18:35,748
[Clears throat]
Reward him.

193
00:18:35,998 --> 00:18:37,582
Man:
Just a sec.

194
00:18:38,165 --> 00:18:39,540
Who killed him?

195
00:18:39,707 --> 00:18:40,748
I did.

196
00:18:40,873 --> 00:18:42,582
You? Really, huh?

197
00:18:43,873 --> 00:18:47,082
He must be an AWOL.
Cut off a dead man's head.

198
00:18:48,665 --> 00:18:50,165
Man in wagon:
Behead him.

199
00:18:53,665 --> 00:18:55,582
That's not true!

200
00:19:02,748 --> 00:19:04,957
[Yelling]
[Sword slashing]

201
00:19:06,332 --> 00:19:09,457
[Water dripping]

202
00:19:26,706 --> 00:19:28,248
Where's the horse?

203
00:19:28,665 --> 00:19:31,790
[Breathing heavily]

204
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:47,706
[Yelling]

205
00:19:49,081 --> 00:19:51,373
Wei's General: You gonna have to
kill me if you don't let me go.

206
00:19:51,540 --> 00:19:53,415
Or I'll kill you in a heart beat.

207
00:19:54,373 --> 00:19:55,956
Big Soldier:
Kill, kill, kill.

208
00:19:56,165 --> 00:19:57,498
I grow farms.

209
00:19:57,706 --> 00:20:00,498
I don't kill and I don't want to kill.

210
00:20:00,623 --> 00:20:02,498
Big Brother:
You're getting me mad.

211
00:20:03,331 --> 00:20:04,706
I'm not gonna kill you.

212
00:20:04,873 --> 00:20:07,081
Big Soldier: Can't believe
I just got fooled by some woman.

213
00:20:08,331 --> 00:20:11,498
I gave her food to eat,
and she gave me pill to swallow.

214
00:20:12,165 --> 00:20:15,915
Wei's General: You deceived her first,
so it sounds fair.

215
00:20:16,540 --> 00:20:18,873
Big Soldier:
She should have hit you instead.

216
00:20:19,165 --> 00:20:20,873
Stupid helmet.

217
00:20:23,956 --> 00:20:26,456
What did she say to you last night?

218
00:20:27,706 --> 00:20:31,165
[Chuckling]
You small potato.

219
00:20:33,248 --> 00:20:36,373
[Instrumental music playing]

220
00:20:37,915 --> 00:20:40,248
Prince:
Who's stronger, me or him?

221
00:20:40,331 --> 00:20:41,415
Wu:
He's a natural.

222
00:20:41,581 --> 00:20:44,123
Prince: So I'm nowhere to compete with him?
Wu: You're too soft and he got the heart.

223
00:20:44,248 --> 00:20:46,123
To become the King,

224
00:20:48,831 --> 00:20:50,873
you must learn from him.

225
00:20:51,165 --> 00:20:53,873
Wu: I'll take a unit and head for Liang's.
Why don't you go back...

226
00:20:53,998 --> 00:20:56,498
Prince:
I won't go back until I see him.

227
00:20:57,206 --> 00:20:58,456
Big Soldier:
You know what,

228
00:20:58,581 --> 00:21:00,790
I've been looking forward to

229
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:04,706
life of peace and farms to grow
for 20 years.

230
00:21:13,165 --> 00:21:16,290
[Instrumental music playing]

231
00:21:34,165 --> 00:21:35,206
[Music stops]

232
00:21:35,415 --> 00:21:39,081
Soldier: The wagon is not here.
The rope was cut off.

233
00:21:45,748 --> 00:21:47,331
[Sighs]

234
00:21:49,206 --> 00:21:50,331
Hey.

235
00:21:53,790 --> 00:21:56,165
Hey. Hey?

236
00:21:56,373 --> 00:21:59,498
[Instrumental music playing]

237
00:22:07,498 --> 00:22:09,581
[Spitting]

238
00:22:09,790 --> 00:22:13,498
Big Soldier: Stop playing dead.
I'm too smart for that.

239
00:22:16,498 --> 00:22:18,040
[Music stops]

240
00:22:19,081 --> 00:22:21,206
[Horse running]

241
00:22:41,248 --> 00:22:43,039
We better stay away from the main road.

242
00:22:43,248 --> 00:22:44,789
Let's take a detour.

243
00:22:44,914 --> 00:22:49,081
Like this track.
Just don't lose the map.

244
00:22:53,289 --> 00:22:55,706
Strong liquor. Must be Liang's.

245
00:22:57,956 --> 00:23:03,664
<i>[Big Soldier singing] One small track
leads the way to home.</i>

246
00:23:12,039 --> 00:23:13,831
Wei's General:
What now?

247
00:23:15,998 --> 00:23:20,581
Like my dad said, step in shit.
Something good awaits me.

248
00:23:21,081 --> 00:23:22,456
Wei's General:
It's an ambush.

249
00:23:22,664 --> 00:23:24,831
Big Soldier:
Yeah, right.

250
00:23:30,206 --> 00:23:33,331
Bum leader:
What's loaded on that wagon?

251
00:23:33,539 --> 00:23:35,873
- Nothing particular.
- Rip him.

252
00:23:36,998 --> 00:23:39,081
Rip him off!
[Instrumental music playing]

253
00:23:42,623 --> 00:23:45,039
Big Soldier: Wait, wait...
Bum leader: Who are you?

254
00:23:45,289 --> 00:23:46,914
[Music pauses]
A General.

255
00:23:49,081 --> 00:23:51,331
Says you.

256
00:23:52,873 --> 00:23:54,998
Beat him.
Wei's General: Hmm?

257
00:23:55,206 --> 00:23:57,164
Beat him down.
