771
01:07:56,952 --> 01:07:59,869
<i>Soils are rich there</i>

772
01:08:00,035 --> 01:08:01,619
Wei's General:
You're loosing it.

773
01:08:02,494 --> 01:08:04,869
Pretty good. My dad said,

774
01:08:05,077 --> 01:08:08,577
as long as you still alive,
it's pretty good.

775
01:08:08,827 --> 01:08:10,160
Must I become the King?

776
01:08:10,285 --> 01:08:13,743
You'll be a good King.
It's a good thing for Wei.

777
01:08:13,827 --> 01:08:17,452
Are you trying to convince me
to kill him without a blink of an eye?

778
01:08:17,618 --> 01:08:21,160
Wu: We've gone this far,
this is the only way out.

779
01:08:21,368 --> 01:08:24,368
Okay, how can he die

780
01:08:26,035 --> 01:08:28,077
with dignity?

781
01:08:29,285 --> 01:08:30,743
Wei's General:
What are you thinking?

782
01:08:32,243 --> 01:08:33,660
Rapeseed flower.

783
01:08:36,452 --> 01:08:38,368
I'm thinking about growing rapeseed.

784
01:08:38,493 --> 01:08:39,618
Why?

785
01:08:39,827 --> 01:08:40,785
Why what?

786
01:08:40,993 --> 01:08:44,160
Why am I being stuck
in a place like this?

787
01:08:44,535 --> 01:08:48,077
I should be the one who brings
all the Dukes to their knees.

788
01:08:48,327 --> 01:08:50,660
And then have a huge tomb
made for me.

789
01:08:50,868 --> 01:08:54,493
Have my own treasure
buried with me.

790
01:08:55,327 --> 01:08:57,993
Now they can't even
find my corpse.

791
01:08:58,618 --> 01:09:03,868
Yeah, the rest of reward money
would go to my new pharmacy store.

792
01:09:04,077 --> 01:09:07,410
To be honest, your drugs worked.

793
01:09:07,785 --> 01:09:11,535
I'm appointing you as
The Minister for Health.

794
01:09:11,618 --> 01:09:14,243
[Chuckling]

795
01:09:16,285 --> 01:09:20,993
You know what, if it wasn't the wars,
we could have been buddies.

796
01:09:21,743 --> 01:09:23,285
Perhaps.

797
01:09:24,868 --> 01:09:26,827
If you make it out alive,

798
01:09:27,452 --> 01:09:30,743
will you promise me one thing?

799
01:09:30,952 --> 01:09:32,202
Shoot.

800
01:09:34,452 --> 01:09:37,660
Never invade my nation, Liang.

801
01:09:44,410 --> 01:09:45,868
[Sighs]

802
01:09:46,202 --> 01:09:49,952
I give you 10 years of truce.
[Chuckling]

803
01:09:50,368 --> 01:09:54,035
Sounds tricky.
You have an agreement.

804
01:09:57,827 --> 01:09:59,785
And you need to promise me one thing.

805
01:09:59,868 --> 01:10:00,827
Shoot.

806
01:10:00,910 --> 01:10:02,785
If you ever make it out alive,

807
01:10:03,660 --> 01:10:05,618
you must tell them that

808
01:10:07,952 --> 01:10:09,368
I died fighting.

809
01:10:10,035 --> 01:10:12,993
I died fighting for my people.

810
01:10:13,910 --> 01:10:16,243
I've done nothing disgraceful
to Wei.

811
01:10:17,743 --> 01:10:23,493
We all bite the dust,
but not our flag.

812
01:10:25,952 --> 01:10:27,785
Don't lie to me,

813
01:10:28,660 --> 01:10:30,702
you small potato.

814
01:10:31,743 --> 01:10:33,868
Being a small potato...

815
01:10:34,327 --> 01:10:36,993
sounds pretty good.

816
01:10:40,243 --> 01:10:41,702
[Sighs]

817
01:10:53,160 --> 01:10:57,327
[Crowd cheering in distance]

818
01:10:58,160 --> 01:11:02,327
[Crowd chuckling in distance]

819
01:11:16,910 --> 01:11:18,452
[Sighs]

820
01:11:26,993 --> 01:11:28,577
Ha!

821
01:11:48,160 --> 01:11:49,410
[Pulling bow string]

822
01:11:52,326 --> 01:11:55,660
[Gasping]

823
01:11:56,160 --> 01:12:00,868
[Sparrow trilling]

824
01:12:05,118 --> 01:12:07,118
[Exhales heavily]

825
01:12:18,660 --> 01:12:20,535
Hey! Hey!

826
01:12:20,951 --> 01:12:22,535
Ow!

827
01:12:22,868 --> 01:12:24,451
Wake up.

828
01:12:25,160 --> 01:12:26,743
[Splashing]

829
01:12:27,785 --> 01:12:31,951
[Breathing heavily]
[Cheerful music playing]

830
01:12:32,826 --> 01:12:36,285
[Gasping]

831
01:12:37,326 --> 01:12:41,493
[Gasping]

832
01:12:43,951 --> 01:12:48,035
Big Solider:
Dad, I'm alive!

833
01:12:49,201 --> 01:12:51,201
Thanks Heaven!

834
01:12:51,618 --> 01:12:53,993
Thanks Heaven!

835
01:12:55,493 --> 01:12:58,410
You know what, this is
Three Legs Cave.

836
01:12:58,535 --> 01:13:00,993
There is a fisherman's village nearby.
I'll go get a boat.

837
01:13:01,285 --> 01:13:02,618
It'll take half a day to get there.

838
01:13:02,826 --> 01:13:04,285
To where?

839
01:13:04,493 --> 01:13:07,285
To Liang, where else could it be?

840
01:13:08,035 --> 01:13:13,118
<i>Don't think about running away.
You can't survive an hour without me.</i>

841
01:13:20,701 --> 01:13:22,076
Big Soldier:
Quick, quick!

842
01:13:23,035 --> 01:13:24,076
Go hide!

843
01:13:24,285 --> 01:13:25,451
Hide from what?

844
01:13:25,660 --> 01:13:29,243
Just hide.
[Horse whinnying]

845
01:13:29,535 --> 01:13:31,160
Hold me up.

846
01:13:38,910 --> 01:13:40,201
Wei's General:
Little brother.

847
01:13:41,160 --> 01:13:43,035
Big Soldier:
Little brother?

848
01:13:44,451 --> 01:13:46,076
He's your brother?

849
01:13:46,243 --> 01:13:48,743
You've been chasing me for days.
Don't you get tired?

850
01:13:48,951 --> 01:13:49,910
Prince.

851
01:13:50,076 --> 01:13:51,285
Big Soldier:
Prince?

852
01:13:51,493 --> 01:13:52,993
Why the mourning bandana?

853
01:13:53,243 --> 01:13:54,826
It's for our father.

854
01:13:54,993 --> 01:13:57,993
Wei's General: He was very sick
when I left for battles. It's you.

855
01:13:58,160 --> 01:14:01,660
It's fate. You just cared about
waging wars to please the old man.

856
01:14:01,868 --> 01:14:04,951
If I hadn't upset him by making
peace arrangement with Liang,

857
01:14:05,118 --> 01:14:06,576
I would have been the Prince.

858
01:14:06,743 --> 01:14:09,368
You set the ambush to make sure
I'd get killed.

859
01:14:10,035 --> 01:14:11,660
Something going on between you two

860
01:14:11,826 --> 01:14:13,743
and we Liang paid with 2,000 lives.

861
01:14:13,951 --> 01:14:15,201
You're not authorized to talk to me.

862
01:14:15,410 --> 01:14:17,326
You're not authorized to talk to me.

863
01:14:18,660 --> 01:14:21,076
- Leave him out of this.
- But he's the enemy.

864
01:14:21,201 --> 01:14:23,160
He wants me to live,
but you wants me to die.

865
01:14:23,243 --> 01:14:28,243
Come on. Use that crossbow I gave you
and claim the throne of Wei.

866
01:14:31,576 --> 01:14:33,660
[Sighs]

867
01:14:35,118 --> 01:14:37,118
Wu:
You're still too soft-hearted.

868
01:14:40,243 --> 01:14:41,785
Your sword.

869
01:14:41,910 --> 01:14:45,535
Wu:
If you don't kill him, he will kill you.

870
01:14:46,493 --> 01:14:48,576
Only one of you will become the King.

871
01:14:51,493 --> 01:14:55,451
Um, that's doesn't make any sense,
why one of you brothers must die?

872
01:14:55,535 --> 01:14:58,868
- It's none of your business.
- You guys are complicating things.

873
01:14:58,868 --> 01:15:03,993
- I said "it's none of your business!"
- It's all because of that nosy baldhead.

874
01:15:05,743 --> 01:15:07,326
I'm done talking.

875
01:15:07,743 --> 01:15:10,951
[Horses whinnying]
[Instrumental music playing]

876
01:15:11,284 --> 01:15:15,451
[Horses whinnying]
[Speaking foreign language]

877
01:15:19,909 --> 01:15:22,534
He really looks upset.
Maybe we should go now.

878
01:15:28,993 --> 01:15:30,534
I'm really messed up big time.

879
01:15:30,743 --> 01:15:33,659
You do what you got to do, Master.

880
01:15:42,201 --> 01:15:44,409
[Arrow cracks]
Aah!

881
01:15:47,118 --> 01:15:49,618
[Speaking foreign language]

882
01:15:54,909 --> 01:15:57,534
Hey, can we go now, eh?

883
01:16:02,409 --> 01:16:03,993
[Sword slashes]

884
01:16:24,409 --> 01:16:27,493
[Pounding]

885
01:16:27,743 --> 01:16:29,284
[Sword scrapes]

886
01:16:43,784 --> 01:16:46,368
Aah!

887
01:16:47,326 --> 01:16:48,868
Aah!

888
01:17:09,493 --> 01:17:11,076
Huh?

889
01:17:14,201 --> 01:17:16,784
[Sighs]

890
01:17:22,409 --> 01:17:25,534
General!
Behind you!

891
01:17:28,993 --> 01:17:30,034
[Chuckling]

892
01:17:30,243 --> 01:17:31,909
It's none of my business.

893
01:17:34,909 --> 01:17:38,576
[Moaning]
What a pity.

894
01:17:38,868 --> 01:17:43,034
[Gasping]

895
01:17:58,576 --> 01:18:00,243
Whoa!

896
01:18:03,868 --> 01:18:07,118
[Groaning]

897
01:18:07,326 --> 01:18:10,451
[Weapon swinging]

898
01:18:21,076 --> 01:18:22,618
Ouch!

899
01:18:23,576 --> 01:18:25,659
Not even one small rock?

900
01:18:42,951 --> 01:18:46,076
[Gasping]

901
01:18:50,534 --> 01:18:52,117
Ow!

902
01:18:52,534 --> 01:18:54,076
Don't get any closer,

903
01:18:54,326 --> 01:18:56,409
or you'd get blind.

904
01:18:58,576 --> 01:19:00,451
<i>Big brother!</i>

905
01:19:32,242 --> 01:19:36,076
[Screaming]

906
01:19:37,617 --> 01:19:39,492
[Yelling in anger]

907
01:19:45,034 --> 01:19:46,784
[Yelling in distance]

908
01:19:51,701 --> 01:19:53,034
Whoa!

909
01:20:00,117 --> 01:20:02,409
[Gasping]

910
01:20:06,992 --> 01:20:09,076
Stop!
[Music stops]

911
01:20:10,242 --> 01:20:11,701
[Gasping]

912
01:20:11,909 --> 01:20:15,034
I'm the one you should kill.

913
01:20:15,534 --> 01:20:18,367
I'm the one you should kill.

914
01:20:18,867 --> 01:20:23,867
Me and my brother,
only one will walk out here alive.

915
01:20:25,659 --> 01:20:29,867
You don't understand
what I'm saying, do you? huh?

916
01:20:33,159 --> 01:20:35,534
How about this, huh? Ah!

917
01:20:35,826 --> 01:20:37,742
This is what I got to do.

918
01:20:37,909 --> 01:20:39,201
<i>Little brother!</i>

919
01:20:45,909 --> 01:20:47,201
Big brother,

920
01:20:47,992 --> 01:20:50,617
am I dying with dignity?

921
01:20:52,659 --> 01:20:57,284
Sorry about our big boat.

922
01:20:57,409 --> 01:21:01,034
We can never build it together.

923
01:21:02,492 --> 01:21:05,659
[Breathing heavily]

924
01:21:48,992 --> 01:21:50,284
Do me a favor.

925
01:21:51,784 --> 01:21:53,617
Help me bury him.

926
01:21:59,284 --> 01:22:03,826
We must carry on, General.
We got half day.

927
01:22:04,742 --> 01:22:08,075
Sorry, I mean Prince.

928
01:22:13,617 --> 01:22:16,784
Your Wei's liquor is not strong enough.

929
01:22:18,242 --> 01:22:20,450
I know what you're thinking.

930
01:22:20,617 --> 01:22:23,784
I also know what you're thinking.

931
01:22:25,867 --> 01:22:29,659
- Pretty good.
- We're still alive.

932
01:22:31,867 --> 01:22:36,367
You two reminded me
of my own brothers.

933
01:22:36,659 --> 01:22:38,117
Wei's Prince:
They were good soldiers.

934
01:22:38,325 --> 01:22:40,534
Big Soldier: In fact,
I wanted to be a good soldier.

935
01:22:41,992 --> 01:22:45,992
The first time we enlisted,
we 3 brothers got no choice.

936
01:22:46,242 --> 01:22:48,409
The first tour lasted for 3 years.

937
01:22:48,784 --> 01:22:50,325
When we came back,

938
01:22:51,284 --> 01:22:53,367
our village had been burnt to ground.

939
01:22:54,242 --> 01:22:56,409
We became homeless.

940
01:22:56,992 --> 01:23:00,034
Before my dad died, he told us
[Slow music playing]

941
01:23:00,242 --> 01:23:03,409
we had served our country.

942
01:23:04,409 --> 01:23:08,992
But when the wars will end?

943
01:23:10,325 --> 01:23:15,034
And he said, "kids, listen,

944
01:23:18,075 --> 01:23:20,492
one of you 3 brothers must live,

945
01:23:25,034 --> 01:23:27,950
in order to raise kids for our family."

946
01:23:29,325 --> 01:23:32,575
[Sobbing]
Now I'm the only one left.

947
01:23:36,867 --> 01:23:41,950
Having you is my biggest luck ever.

948
01:23:44,034 --> 01:23:48,200
[Sobbing continues]

949
01:23:49,992 --> 01:23:54,784
I can't say the same thing about my luck.

950
01:23:55,534 --> 01:23:59,700
[Woman singing in distance]

951
01:24:02,742 --> 01:24:06,992
[Singing continues]

952
01:24:10,742 --> 01:24:12,159
Wei's Prince:
Don't ask.

953
01:24:12,784 --> 01:24:15,117
What she said to me the other night:

954
01:24:16,825 --> 01:24:18,700
"kama".

955
01:24:18,909 --> 01:24:20,825
[Sighs]

956
01:24:20,992 --> 01:24:23,117
What a little potato.

957
01:24:25,242 --> 01:24:28,784
[Singing continues]

958
01:24:32,825 --> 01:24:35,950
Shen Shu, Mt. Phoenix.

959
01:24:40,950 --> 01:24:46,909
"Peace"

960
01:25:01,867 --> 01:25:03,450
"Mt. Liang"

961
01:25:03,617 --> 01:25:07,200
You know what,
after this turn is Liang's soil.

962
01:25:12,159 --> 01:25:15,825
My brother wanted to befriend
Liang, maybe he's right.

963
01:25:15,992 --> 01:25:19,534
If Liang's Duke spare my life, may be we could
work something out for allying each other.

964
01:25:19,659 --> 01:25:21,200
Maybe, maybe.

965
01:25:23,242 --> 01:25:24,909
Maybe it's too late.

966
01:25:25,825 --> 01:25:27,409
Maybe.

967
01:25:38,867 --> 01:25:42,408
[Breathing heavily]

968
01:25:42,658 --> 01:25:45,325
Nothing feels like home!

969
01:25:49,408 --> 01:25:51,533
That's your secret belt...

970
01:26:00,367 --> 01:26:02,158
I was wrong about you.

971
01:26:03,158 --> 01:26:06,325
Never thought you could make
this journey for both of us.

972
01:26:07,117 --> 01:26:10,617
Now, am I your captive or enemy?

973
01:26:13,867 --> 01:26:15,533
[Sword scrapes]

974
01:26:17,908 --> 01:26:20,283
Neither. Just go.

975
01:26:22,867 --> 01:26:25,992
Hurry. Before I change my mind.

976
01:26:29,992 --> 01:26:31,367
Why?

977
01:26:32,658 --> 01:26:34,408
You 2 brothers...

978
01:26:34,617 --> 01:26:36,575
one must live.

979
01:26:36,783 --> 01:26:38,992
[Grunting]

980
01:26:47,367 --> 01:26:48,992
Can I count on your word?

981
01:26:49,533 --> 01:26:50,825
What you mean?

982
01:26:51,033 --> 01:26:52,825
10 years of truce!

983
01:26:53,033 --> 01:26:56,408
Absolutely!
You have my word!

984
01:27:00,742 --> 01:27:02,367
Don't forget...

985
01:27:02,825 --> 01:27:06,158
that medal you took from me,
it's worth a fortunate.

986
01:27:06,492 --> 01:27:09,908
It can get your farmland and money.

987
01:27:11,533 --> 01:27:13,158
I found it.

988
01:27:13,783 --> 01:27:15,783
[Sighs]

989
01:27:16,033 --> 01:27:18,700
I might not live long enough...

990
01:27:20,117 --> 01:27:23,783
Now I'm empty-handed.
Pretty good.

991
01:27:27,200 --> 01:27:29,325
<i>Boy:
Run.</i>

992
01:27:30,742 --> 01:27:32,908
Run away now.

993
01:27:50,325 --> 01:27:52,700
[Soldiers cheering]

994
01:28:02,825 --> 01:28:07,533
[Cheering continues]

995
01:28:10,658 --> 01:28:12,742
[Horse whinnying]

996
01:28:13,533 --> 01:28:15,158
Officer:
Ask him to surrender.

997
01:28:17,408 --> 01:28:21,117
Liang has been destroyed.
Knee down and surrender.

998
01:28:22,992 --> 01:28:24,658
Liang is gone?

999
01:28:25,867 --> 01:28:27,200
How could that possible?

1000
01:28:27,367 --> 01:28:30,575
Officer: Liang refused to surrender.
So we, from Qin, destroyed it.

1001
01:28:30,742 --> 01:28:34,408
- Your units have been completely eliminated.
Qin's soldier: On your knee. Last chance.

1002
01:28:34,575 --> 01:28:36,492
Big Soldier:
All units wiped out?

1003
01:28:36,700 --> 01:28:38,283
No more Liang.

1004
01:28:38,742 --> 01:28:39,992
"Qin"

1005
01:28:40,117 --> 01:28:43,533
This is not happening.
[Pulling bow string]

1006
01:28:47,533 --> 01:28:52,325
[No dialogues]

1007
01:28:53,033 --> 01:28:55,450
[Bow shot]

1008
01:28:57,325 --> 01:29:01,492
[Grunts]
[Qin's soldiers chuckling]

1009
01:29:02,742 --> 01:29:04,867
Liang is history.

1010
01:29:06,867 --> 01:29:10,033
I really got nothing left now.

1011
01:29:10,950 --> 01:29:14,033
Qin's officer:
Put the flag down.

1012
01:29:20,616 --> 01:29:23,700
<i>[Prince singing]
One main road</i>

1013
01:29:23,783 --> 01:29:25,825
Qin's officer:
Your units have been wiped out.

1014
01:29:25,908 --> 01:29:28,533
Big Soldier:
That's not entirely true.

1015
01:29:28,658 --> 01:29:29,908
Qin's officer:
Drop your sword.

1016
01:29:30,116 --> 01:29:32,158
I'm still standing!
Give your best shot!

1017
01:29:32,241 --> 01:29:35,950
<i>[Singing]
My home is right at</i>

1018
01:29:38,158 --> 01:29:41,283
<i>the foot of Mt. Liang</i>

1019
01:29:42,033 --> 01:29:50,116
<i>Soils are rich there
5 acres of farms</i>

1020
01:29:51,658 --> 01:29:54,200
<i>5 acres of farm</i>

1021
01:29:54,366 --> 01:29:55,866
Sorry dad,

1022
01:29:56,366 --> 01:30:00,575
guess I'm not gonna raise
any kids now.

1023
01:30:02,825 --> 01:30:06,991
<i>[Singing]
One big river</i>

1024
01:30:07,533 --> 01:30:11,075
<i>leads to my home</i>

1025
01:30:12,408 --> 01:30:16,700
<i>My wife, my kids</i>

1026
01:30:17,116 --> 01:30:20,241
<i>and my big house</i>

1027
01:30:22,241 --> 01:30:26,700
<i>Chickens and ducks are fat</i>

1028
01:30:27,325 --> 01:30:31,366
<i>Cattle is strong</i>

1029
01:30:32,200 --> 01:30:36,700
<i>Grow some bean
white grain</i>

1030
01:30:37,200 --> 01:30:41,408
<i>and rapeseed flower</i>

1031
01:30:45,658 --> 01:30:47,741
[Spring bouncing]

